Date: 0/0/1934
Source: NZ Journal of Agriculture
Author:
Vol / Page: XLIX/152
Edition:
Quote: There are several species of <i>Pimelea</i> in New Zealand... It is known in New Zealand generally as Strathmore weed, from the name of a Taranaki town where posoning of horses was first recorded.
